  "prompt": "What universities does Sonic Automotive recruit new grads from? What majors are they looking for?",
  "response": "Sonic Automotive, one of the largest automotive retailers in the United States, typically recruits graduates from a variety of universities, often focusing on schools with strong business, finance, marketing, and automotive programs. While the specific universities can vary, Sonic Automotive has been known to recruit from institutions such as:\n\n1. **University of North Carolina at Charlotte** (UNCC) - Given its proximity to Sonic Automotive's headquarters.\n2. **Clemson University** - Known for its strong engineering and business programs.\n3. **University of South Carolina** - Offers robust business and marketing programs.\n4. **Auburn University** - Recognized for its automotive engineering and business programs.\n5. **University of Georgia** - Known for its business and marketing programs.\n6. **North Carolina State University** - Offers strong engineering and business programs.\n\n### Majors They Look For:\nSonic Automotive recruits from a variety of majors, depending on the roles they are looking to fill. Common majors include:\n\n1. **Business Administration/Management** - For roles in dealership management, sales, and operations.\n2. **Finance/Accounting** - For positions in financial analysis, accounting, and corporate finance.\n3. **Marketing** - For roles in digital marketing, advertising, and customer relations.\n4. **Engineering** (particularly Automotive or Mechanical Engineering) - For roles in service, parts, and technical operations.\n5. **Information Technology/Computer Science** - For roles in IT support, software development, and data analysis.\n6. **Hospitality/Communications** - For customer service and client relations roles.\n\n### Recruitment Process:\nSonic Automotive often participates in career fairs, on-campus recruitment events, and partnerships with university career centers to identify and attract top talent. They may also offer internships and co-op programs to students as a pathway to full-time employment after graduation.\n\nFor the most accurate and up-to-date information, it's best to check Sonic Automotive's official careers page or contact their Human Resources department directly.",
  "temperature": 1.0,
